'''Arsamuh''' (also spelled '''Arthamukh''') was the ruler of the [[Afrighids|Afrighid dynasty]] of [[Khwarezm]], ruling during the time of the prophet [[Muhammad]]. Arsamuh was the successor of [[Buzgar]], and was later succeeded by [[Sahr II]].

