{{Infobox Organization |image = Newerapubl.jpg |size = 200px |caption = Bridge Publications, Los Angeles, CA |name = Bridge Publications |formation = 1981 |type = Religious publishing |status = Non-profit |purpose = |headquarters = [[Los Angeles, California]], United States |leader_title = President |leader_name = Blake Silber |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = |website = {{official URL}} |remarks = }}
'''Bridge Publications, Inc.''' (BPI) is the [[Church of Scientology]]'s [[North America]]n publishing corporation. It publishes the [[Scientology]] and other religious works of [[L. Ron Hubbard]]. Outside of North America, this is done under the '''New Era Publications''' name, based in [[Copenhagen]].
It also published Hubbard's fiction and the annual ''[[Writers of the Future]]'' [[science fiction]] [[anthology|anthologies]] until [[2002 in literature|2002]], when [[Galaxy Press]] was established for this purpose.{{Citation needed|date=March 2008}}
Bridge was originally established in 1971 as '''Publications Organization, United States'''.{{Citation needed|date=March 2008}} It moved to its current 273,000 square foot facility location in Los Angeles in 2009. For the first time in its history, all administrative offices, printing and manufacturing areas, and warehousing and delivery is all in one location.
Scientology literature publication has the following divisions: Bridge Publications in Los Angeles serving North America, New Era Publications in Denmark, serving the European and global audience, and Golden Era Productions, which takes care of audio-visual material. Hubbard’s science fiction, fantasy and pulp literature is the domain of the Author Services, Inc.<ref>{{cite book |last=Petersen |first1=Jesper Aagaard |title=Controversial New Religions |work=Oxford University Press |year=2004 |accessdate=2015-12-28 }}</ref>
