{{Quran}}
'''Quranic infallibility''' is a [[doctrine]] central to the [[Muslim]] faith that the [[Quran]] is the [[Infallibility|infallible]] and inerrant word of [[God in Islam|God]] as  revealed to [[Muhammad]] by the [[archangel]] [[Gabriel in Islam|Gabriel]] fourteen hundred years ago.<ref>{{Cite book |url=https://books.google.com.pk/books?id=ZRenjUoud3kC&pg=PA19&dq=quran+infallible+islam&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjlu-_z_8rYAhWDvhQKHX7wBb4Q6AEIMjAC#v=onepage&q=quran%2520infallible%2520islam&f=false |title=What You Need to Know about Islam & Muslims |last=Braswell |first=George W. |date=2000 |publisher=B&H Publishing Group |isbn=9780805418293 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book |url=https://books.google.com.pk/books?id=uSK9tgAACAAJ&dq=Quranic+infallibility&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwj9yP6xhcvYAhUEchQKHZbeBLkQ6AEIPDAE |title=The Holy Quran is Infallible: A Critique of the Book "Is the Qur'an Infallible?" by 'Abdullah 'Abdal-Fadi, a Minister of Christ |last=Anwar |first=Syed Shakeel Ahmed |date=2007 |publisher=Telugu Islamic Publications Trust |isbn=9788188241736 |language=en}}</ref>

