'''The Royal Aal al-Bayt Institute for Islamic Thought ''' is an international [[Islam]]ic non-governmental, independent institute in [[Amman]], Jordan.<ref>[http://www.aalalbayt.org/en/index.html The Royal Aal al-Bayt Institute for Islamic Thought] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131030052414/http://www.aalalbayt.org/en/index.html |date=October 30, 2013 }}</ref>
It is affiliated with the [[Royal Islamic Strategic Studies Centre]].

The late King [[Hussein Bin Talal]] established the Institute in 1980, and entrusted it to Prince [[Prince Hassan bin Talal]]. It passed on to Crown Prince [[Prince Hamzah bin Al Hussein]] on August 8, 1999 and then to Prince [[Ghazi bin Muhammad]], who is the Chair of the Board of Trustees.{{Citation needed|date=May 2014}}

Fellows of the Institute attend a conference every 2–3 years. The last one was held in September 2010, under the title "Islam and the Environment".<ref>[http://www.petra.gov.jo/Public_News/Nws_NewsDetails.aspx?lang=2&site_id=1&NewsID=6088&Type=P Jordan News Agency (Petra) |Aal al-Bayt Institute holds its 15th General Conference] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140508223708/http://www.petra.gov.jo/Public_News/Nws_NewsDetails.aspx?lang=2&site_id=1&NewsID=6088&Type=P |date=May 8, 2014 }}</ref>

The institute was the leading sponsor of the statements, ''The [[Amman Message]]'' and ''[[A Common Word Between Us and You]]''.

